![Qualys]({{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }}
Create a new case in TheHive
In this section, we create a new case in TheHive as a container for our PDF report. The case must be created first to have a case ID to use to upload the file as an attachment. 

Each new report generates a case in TheHive, ensuring that the report is properly attached to the created case for better tracking and organization.

For more information about this endpoint, visit the [API quick reference]({{ $env.API_BASE_URL }}

![Qualys]({{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }}
## Fetch reports from Qualys
For more information about this endpoint, visit the [API quick reference]({{ $env.API_BASE_URL }} The results of the api call are converted from XML to JSON.

![n8n]({{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }}
## Set time Stamp
To ensure we do not duplicate data in TheHive, we set a timestamp like a bookmark for every time we run this workflow. We then use the previous timestamp if available to only get the newest scan results from Qualys.

![TheHive]({{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }}
## Create a new case in TheHive
In this section, we create a new case in TheHive as a container for our PDF report. The case must be created first to have a case ID to use to upload the file as an attachment. Each new report generates a case in TheHive, ensuring that the report is properly attached to the created case for better tracking and organization.

![TheHive]({{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }}
Here we attach the PDF file as an attachment to the Case in TheHive. 

This step automates the attachment of the downloaded report to the created case, ensuring all relevant information is consolidated in one place.
